HEADWORD: Tippling-house
<hw>Tip"pling-house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A house in
which liquors are sold in drams or small quantities, to be drunk on the
premises.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

